{"type":"message","id":"ed57ee37","parentId":"587ada30","timestamp":"2026-05-15T12:57:09.805Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Git status shows only untracked files - no modifications. So the rollback was successful. The AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md are intact (MEMORY.md was never in tts workspace). The evolver tried to modify many files but hit the HARD CAP breach and validation failures, then rolled back. So nothing was actually changed.\n\nBut the evolver went through a full cycle: it scanned 186 session logs, detected signals, attempted mutation, failed due to constraints, and rolled back. This is actually working - it's just that the last attempt failed due to the constraints (155 files > 60 file limit, validation failure).\n\nSo capability-evolver IS working in the sense that it runs, detects signals, attempts evolution, but the cycle failed due to constraint violations. The failure is expected behavior when constraints are breached.\n\n\nThe evolver is functioning as intended - it detected signals, ran a full evolution cycle, hit constraint limits, and successfully rolled back the changes. The \"Not Found\" errors stem from the same constraint violations that caused the cycle to fail in the first place.\n","thinkingSignature":"494531999fbcee45bf8d9162df3be3f8d82235413db196c459d1a834de832356"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_57nzrsped2b2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver/memory/evolution/evolution_solidify_state.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('last_run:', d.get('last_run',{}).get('created_at')); print('outcome:', d.get('last_run',{}).get('outcome_recorded')); print('gene:', d.get('last_run',{}).get('selected_gene_id'))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":821,"output":345,"cacheRead":91136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92302,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead"