{"type":"message","id":"ed6d95d5","parentId":"f4ccfa81","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:01:44.210Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the gene structure. The issue is that `gene_gep_innovate_from_opportunity` matches `user_feature_request` signals, and when it fires, it tries to modify a large number of files (155 files, 33378 lines) because the innovation strategy tends to explore broadly.\n\nThe problem is:\n1. The workspace `/home/halei/workspace/` has many agent workspaces (tts, content, koc, traffic, ops, director, finance, review, agent-orchestrator) \n2. When evolver runs in the workspace-tts or main session scope, it scans sessions and sees feature requests from various agents\n\n\n3. The innovation gene is triggering based on feature requests across all these workspaces, but the blast radius (155 files) far exceeds the 60-file hard cap\n\nThe solution is to set up a cron job that runs `node index.js` periodically (every 2-4 hours) rather than relying on automatic triggering, and adjusting the EVOLVE_STRATEGY to `harden` or `repair-only` to be more conservative. I should check the config to understand how the hard cap and forbidden paths constraints are enforced so I can set more appropriate limits.\n","thinkingSignature":"5aead72a963cc1b3521690104cfcf9674f877de33fc08fddf1897d3b99842597"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qrbk5uc2uqjw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"HARD_CAP\\|max_files\\|forbidden_paths\\|blastRadius\\|constraint\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver/src/ --include=\"*.js\" -l 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qrbk5uc2uqjw_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"60\\|20000\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver/src/ --include=\"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"file\\|cap\\|limit\\|max\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":317,"output":388,"cacheRead":