{"type":"message","id":"bef601fb","parentId":"31146d09","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:04:25.121Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The evolver is stuck in a loop - it keeps trying the same failing gene. The signal \"user_feature_request:给自己取个名字\" (from the dream diary) is a false positive that keeps triggering `innovate` gene, which then fails validation because it tries to modify too many files.\n\nThe core problem is that the evolver is running on a workspace that has 9 sub-workspaces (tts, content, koc, etc.) and its baseline doesn't include these directories. When it tries to \"innovate\", it sees everything as changed.\n\nKey things to fix:\n1. The evolver's baseline should include all the workspace subdirectories\n\n\n2. The `user_feature_request` signal detection is too sensitive - it's picking up dream diary text and misinterpreting it as a legitimate feature request\n3. I need to set up a cron job to run evolver daily while in repair-only mode to prevent this stuck state\n4. The constraint configuration seems to be failing silently even with the harden strategy, so I should investigate what's actually happening with the constraint enforcement\n\nThe real issue is that evolver keeps cycling through the same failed `innovate_from_opportunity` gene because it's stuck in a retry loop. Setting up a daily cron job with `repair-only` mode should break this cycle, and I also need to add those 9 workspace subdirectories to the forbidden_paths so evolver stops treating them as changeable files.\n","thinkingSignature":"aab1806670b4593874c9679f9fa975443288ba7367ce8a726d0ffb70d3cd8dfe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tftl2vne1f0w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver/memory/evolution/evolution_solidify_state.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nlr=d.get('last_run',{})\nprint('gene:', lr.get('selected_gene_id'))\nprint('outcome:', lr.get('outcome_r