{"type":"message","id":"c27f5a76","parentId":"789bf969","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:06:01.106Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The signal is coming from dreaming content - \"叫我老板，给自己取个名字\" from a dream diary entry. This is a false positive from the dreaming system. The evolver is detecting this text as a `user_feature_request` signal.\n\nThe issue is the `high_failure_ratio` and `force_innovation_after_repair_loop` signals - these indicate previous cycles failed. The evolver is in a stuck state.\n\nLet me look at the evolution_narrative.md to understand the full story, then plan the fix.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. Instead of trying to fix the evolver's state, I should:\n\n1. Clear the stuck dreaming session content that generates the false signal\n\n\n2. Reset the evolver's state to clear failure streaks\n3. Set up a cron job to run evolver regularly\n4. Configure it with `harden` strategy to be more conservative\n\nI need to check the evolution_narrative file first to understand what's happening.\n","thinkingSignature":"27bcd1e65a8f2564a936524693654d757f2eaef7083f26368f3df30db19bb493"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s8jp8xgok3ts_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver/memory/evolution/evolution_narrative.md 2>/dev/null | tail -80"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":619,"output":255,"cacheRead":137024,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137898,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778850349610,"responseId":"06564d2ed48bcc3b1678dfdf89578bdd"}}
