{"type":"message","id":"166d3654","parentId":"408b332f","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:09:29.405Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the gateway is back up. The cron list works. Now let me add the evolver cron job. Let me also check what's needed to make the evolver actually work - there was an issue with the signal being stuck. Let me first try to fix that.\n\nBut actually, thinking about this more carefully - the issue is that the evolver reads session logs and the memory/corpus contains that dream diary entry that includes \"给自己取个名字\". This is causing a false positive `user_feature_request` signal.\n\nLet me:\n1. First add the cron job\n2. Then fix the stuck signal by clearing the corrupt session corpus entry or adjusting the evolver state\n\n\n3. Execute the cron job setup now that the gateway is responding again.\n","thinkingSignature":"60c7eb86bfe397f1aa880783cf57780bb74c11fc360aef0f32029778bd3c9f5d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGateway is back! Let me now add the cron job and fix the stuck signal.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7jj1l9iajsxo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 先修复 stuck signal — 清理那个导致误判的 session corpus\n# 把包含\"给自己取个名字\"的 session 文件重命名，跳过它\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.dreams/session-corpus/\nfor f in 2026-05-13.txt 2026-05-14.txt 2026-05-15.txt; do\n  if [ -f \"$f\" ] && grep -q \"给自己取个名字\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"Renaming $f\"\n    mv \"$f\" \"$f.skip\"\n  fi\ndone\necho \"Done. Remaining session corpus files:\"\nls *.txt 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":258,"output":340,"cacheRead":140480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141078,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778850554753,"responseId":"06564dfb56033ff9b3d352b9ea24b9e3"}}
