{"type":"message","id":"ff3745e6","parentId":"8d04341e","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:17:35.911Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the evolver is still picking up \"user_feature_request\" from the current session. The signal is being parsed from the transcript of this very conversation - the user is asking \"我想知道这个功能的自动迭代是否有作用\" and the evolver interprets this as a user_feature_request.\n\nThe problem is fundamental: the evolver scans session logs and picks up user messages as signals. Any time we discuss evolver in this session, it picks up that signal again.\n\nThe issue is:\n1. The evolver scans session logs\n2. Your current message \"我想知道这个功能的自动迭代是否有作用\" gets picked up as `user_feature_request` \n\n\n3. This triggers `gene_gep_innovate_from_opportunity`\n4. The gene tries to make massive changes (155 files) \n5. Fails HARD CAP BREACH\n6. Rollback\n\nThe problem is that the evolver is reading from the current session logs which contain the current conversation. I could try using `EVOLVER_SESSION_SCOPE` to exclude the current session, or set up a filter in the session scanning, but fundamentally this is the core issue - the evolver scans recent sessions and gets confused by signals from this very conversation.\n\nThe real fix would be either excluding the current session's transcript from what gets scanned, or using `--session-scope` to target only specific agents' logs, but the evolver keeps reading the current session and generating those massive 155-file changes. The \"user_feature_request\" signal is just the user asking if the feature works, not an actual request for new functionality. I need to either stop evolver from scanning the current session, scope it to only look at session archives, or filter out these conversational signals before they trigger the gene.\n","thinkingSignature":"6b324e1eb13923a307426f77b6bbc4662bfa28612937f74aac96aabe17c8666c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z87ptqd6ve75_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看当前 session 是什么时候创建的\nls -la ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/*.jsonl 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# 看有哪些 session 文件\nls ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"\\.jsonl$\" | wc -l"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":361,"output":450,"cacheRead":131072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131883,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778851037149,"responseId":"06564fddac733b678a578e20a9cfbd4b"}}
