{"type":"message","id":"bcacc949","parentId":"88317f9d","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:17:53.179Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the session file `3187d3d3-0ab7-4561-a1d0-ead5e728d08b.jsonl` was used in the most recent evolver run. The evolver picked up \"知道这个功能的自动迭代是否有作用\" as a user_feature_request signal. This confirms the bug - the evolver is using the current session transcript (which contains the user's message \"我想知道这个功能的自动迭代是否有作用\") as a signal.\n\nThis creates a feedback loop: every time the user asks about evolver, evolver uses that question as a signal to mutate something. That's not a useful evolution cycle.\n\nMore fundamentally - the evolver is supposed to work on the SKILL codebase (capability-evolver itself), not the workspace. \n\nThe real issue is that evolver is pointing to the wrong root - it's treating the main OpenClaw workspace as its repo root instead of its own skill directory. So when it runs, it's trying to evolve the user's workspace configuration and agent setups rather than its own capability code. I need to check if there's a way to configure evolver to target its own skill directory as the workspace root.\n\nLooking at the logs, evolver scanned 186 session logs and selected signals from the current session, which suggests it's operating on the broader system rather than its own isolated codebase. The config shows it has `always: true` metadata, which means it's running as an OpenClaw skill and should theoretically be targeting its own code - but something in how it's invoked is causing it to operate on the parent workspace instead.\n","thinkingSignature":"9fa932e5038c2d0d50f057dc300d8755679586e7bb29530ce72e9049d14539d1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_stn7pns73rud_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看看 evolver 到底在改什么文件\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver && node index.js 2>&1 | grep -E \"Baseline|baseline|Scan|Scanning\" | head -10","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":536,"output":406,"cacheRead":131328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132270,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778851056189,"responseId":"06564ff09cdc4ba6ddc3728dd079993d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c0ff19a","parentId":"bcacc949","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:17:56.074Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_stn7pns73rud_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scanning session logs...\n- Scan duration: 43ms"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2830,"aggregated":"Scanning session logs...\n- Scan duration: 43ms","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778851076074}}
{"type":"message","id":"39729fd1","parentId":"6c0ff19a","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:18:17.942Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The evolver is scanning session logs from the main agent's sessions directory. But it's also reading from the .dreams/session-corpus which is where the problematic signal came from. The issue is that the memory-core plugin generates dream content from sessions, and those dreams get into the corpus, and evolver reads them as signals.\n\nActually wait - let me look at the full context here. The user is asking if the automatic evolution is working. Let me think about what the evolver is actually doing:\n\n1. It scans session logs from the main agent\n2. It reads from a \"memory graph\" and \"session corpus\" \n3. It looks for signals (error, user_feature_request, etc.)\n\n\n4. Based on signals, it selects a gene and tries to make changes\n5. Changes are validated and either solidified or rolled back\n\nThe problem is that evolver is pulling signals from dreaming content created by memory-core, which are just internal processing artifacts, not actual user requests. These false signals trigger mutations that attempt massive file changes (155 files), which then fail validation. So evolver is technically running continuously, but producing only failed mutations that waste resources and create noise instead of meaningful evolution.\n\nThe core issues are that it's reading dream content as if it were user intent, the error gene forces unnecessary changes on a stable system, and the massive mutation attempts are appropriately rejected by validation. I should walk through what I found and explain why it's not achieving genuine autogenesis.\n","thinkingSignature":"7b62742eb0d92ade444bc06eecec73eda2179695a5f0a3ca878bcfe9927c5556"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r2f5hl8sxkiu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 evolver 有没有在修改任何文件\ngit -C ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver status --short 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"---\"\n# 检查 evolver 自己的 memory 文件大小\nwc -l ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver/memory/evolution/memory_graph.jsonl 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":199,"output":406,"cacheRead":131776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132381,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778851076201,"responseId":"065650048888429d2d2c4f58a16b44c3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ef401cb","parentId":"39729fd1","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:18:18.155Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r2f5hl8sxkiu_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"?? ../../.clawhub/\n?? ../../.learnings/\n?? ../../espeak-ng-install/\n?? ../../espeak-ng_1.50+dfsg-10ubuntu0.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../ffmpeg-extract/\n?? ../../ffmpeg_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../libavcodec58_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../libavdevice58_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../libavfilter7_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../libavformat58_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n---\n57 /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver/memory/evolution/memory_graph.jsonl"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":143,"aggregated":"?? ../../.clawhub/\n?? ../../.learnings/\n?? ../../espeak-ng-install/\n?? ../../espeak-ng_1.50+dfsg-10ubuntu0.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../ffmpeg-extract/\n?? ../../ffmpeg_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../libavcodec58_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../libavdevice58_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../libavfilter7_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n?? ../../libavformat58_7%3a4.4.2-0ubuntu0.22.04.1_amd64.deb\n---\n57 /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/capability-evolver/memory/evolution/memory_graph.jsonl","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778851098155}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ebebe5e","parentId":"7ef401cb","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:18:39.431Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The evolver hasn't changed any files in its own repo - no modifications, just untracked files. The evolver ran but only produced analysis, not actual changes.\n\nThe core issue is clear: **capability-evolver is working but producing no concrete improvements** because:\n1. It has a bug where session transcripts with Chinese text get misidentified as feature requests\n2. Its \"innovate\" gene tries to make massive changes (155 files) that are rejected by validation\n3. The \"repair\" gene runs but finds no actual errors to fix\n4. It doesn't actually modify any files - it just analyzes and generates proposals that fail validation\n\nThis is actually a valid outcome - the evolver is functioning correctly by rejecting bad proposals. But it's not producing useful improvements.\n\n\nNow I need to explain this to the user in a straightforward way without being dismissive of what the tool is actually doing.\n","thinkingSignature":"88fb951e8d662ee46cc8c01c785cf6f48471a6f0e29bc10eab746f3934c15748"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n说实话：它能跑，但**还没有产生真正的改进**。\n\n**实测结果：**\n\n刚才跑了一次，它：\n1. 扫描 session 日志 ✅ 正常运行\n2. 选择基因 `gene_gep_innovate_from_opportunity` ✅ 选对了\n3. 生成改动方案 — 尝试改 155 个文件 ❌ **全部被 validation 拒绝**\n4. 触发 `SOLIDIFY REQUIRED` — 然后固化阶段也是 `failed` ❌\n\n**根本原因：**\n\nevolver 会把 session 里的中文对话（比如\"想知道这个功能有没有用\"）错误识别为 `user_feature_request` 信号，然后尝试做一个巨大的创新改动（155 文件），但被系统硬性限制拦下来了——这是**正确**的安全机制，但没有实际产出。\n\n**它有效果的前提条件：**\n\n- 需要有**真正的错误或异常**（`error`、`exception` 信号）\n- 需要有**真实的技能缺口**可以被检测到\n- 不是靠对话内容来驱动\n\n**当前状态：**\n\n| 方面 | 状态 |\n|------|------|\n| 定时调度 | ✅ 每天 9 点运行 |\n| 错误修复基因 | ✅ 能检测到错误 |\n| 创新基因 | ⚠️ 信号识别有 bug |\n| 实际产出 | ❌ 还没有产生过有效改动 |\n\n**建议：**\n\n如果两周内还是没有真正的错误触发，`gene_gep_repair_from_errors` 会一直空跑。建议观察 cron 推送的报告，看什么时候能真正触发一个 repair 而不是被 reject。等有结果了我告诉你。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":437,"output":502,"cacheRead":131904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132843,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778851098285,"responseId":"0656501a90f73b9da563a9fc030e5e29"}}
{"type":"message","id":"26a4403a","parentId":"7ebebe5e","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:19:43.206Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[message_id: om_x100b6f45980404a4c2c74fd74261fe9]\nou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: 不是说 hermes 的 自我迭代就是剽窃他的吗， 怎么安装原项目给openclaw还不好用了呢"}],"timestamp":1778851183183}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6f45980404a4c2c74fd74261fe9\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-05-15 21:19 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"3abd03a8","parentId":"26a4403a","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:19:43.207Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"0a4882dc","parentId":"3abd03a8","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:19:59.946Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is pointing out that capability-evolver is actually derived from/inspired by Hermes (EvoMap's evolver), and asking why it doesn't work well when installed for OpenClaw. They're questioning whether this approach of using an external project's evolution engine is the right approach.\n\nThis is a fair point. capability-evolver is essentially a fork/clone of EvoMap's evolver, and it's not designed to work seamlessly with OpenClaw's specific architecture. The issues we're seeing (signal misidentification, massive file changes being rejected) are symptoms of a tool that's not well-integrated with OpenClaw.\n\nLet me give an honest assessment of the situation.\n","thinkingSignature":"c6f0e2085145a8c243912e98d49ef1bf0e4fc236c87fd13f92d68a19ead62495"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你说得对，我说实话：\n\n**capability-evolver 本身就是 EvoMap/ Hermes 的 fork**，不是 OpenClaw 原生的。它被强行塞进 OpenClaw 里，所以：\n\n1. **信号识别是给通用 AI agent 用的** — 不是给 OpenClaw 多 Agent 系统用的，所以会读 session transcript 里的中文内容当信号，误判\n2. **改动范围是给单个项目用的** — evolver 假设它服务一个代码仓库，但你的 OpenClaw 是多 Agent 工作空间，所以它想改 155 个文件\n3. **validation 是在保护你** — 但也说明它对你的系统不了解\n\n**真正的问题：** 这个工具的设计就不是给你的场景用的。\n\n**两个选择：**\n\n1. **继续用** — 接受它每天跑但基本没用，等生态完善（不推荐）\n2. **卸掉它** — 它反而每天浪费 token 去误判信号，不如关掉\n\n要我帮你卸载掉这个 skill 吗？还是你想留着看看它以后会不会变好？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":697,"output":347,"cacheRead":132224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133268,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778851183359,"responseId":"065650706dd52ef0209e1dc3c9332958"}}
