{"type":"message","id":"ab665303","parentId":"18d951f4","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:23:28.827Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_u3x6b4mtpw8a_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: clawhub\ndescription: Search, install, update, sync, or publish agent skills with the ClawHub CLI and registry.\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"clawhub\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"node\",\n              \"kind\": \"node\",\n              \"package\": \"clawhub\",\n              \"bins\": [\"clawhub\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install ClawHub CLI (npm)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# ClawHub CLI\n\nInstall\n\n```bash\nnpm i -g clawhub\n```\n\nAuth (publish)\n\n```bash\nclawhub login\nclawhub whoami\n```\n\nSearch\n\n```bash\nclawhub search \"postgres backups\"\n```\n\nInstall\n\n```bash\nclawhub install my-skill\nclawhub install my-skill --version 1.2.3\n```\n\n\n[28 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778851408827}}
{"type":"message","id":"434b2d81","parentId":"ab665303","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:23:43.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so ClawHub CLI is separate from cocoloop hub. The user is asking about cocoloop (hub.cocoloop.cn) which is a different registry. \n\nWait - let me look at the user's question more carefully. They said \"这个 https://hub.cocoloop.cn/skills/666\" - they want to look at the capability-evolver on cocoloop hub.\n\nAnd they asked \"不是说 hermes 的自我迭代就是剽窃他的吗\" - they're pointing out that Hermes's self-iteration is based on/derived from this, and wondering why the original project (this capability-evolver from cocoloop) doesn't work well with OpenClaw.\n \nNow I'm seeing the version mismatch more clearly - cocoloop has v1.27.3, which is the OpenClaw-adapted version, while the npm package is at 1.67.4, the upstream EvoMap version. These are fundamentally different builds, and the cocoloop version is specifically designed to work with OpenClaw's architecture.\n\nThe user seems to be pointing out that Hermes (EvoMap's implementation) is actually derived from or inspired by this OpenClaw version, not the other way around - so the original capability-evolver on cocoloop predates and informs the Hermes project. They're also wondering why this skill isn't functioning properly, which suggests they might be on an outdated installation or there's a configuration issue with their current setup.\n","thinkingSignature":"8268bb899cccf9f8d982869b24b91bfc5029003f9e9325b5ad53ded9394e1b00"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kj4m2tlvu5lz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查看 clawhub 的配置和 registry\nclawhub --version 2>&1 | head -3\necho \"---\"\nclawhub config list 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":358,"output":366,"cacheRead":137536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138260,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopRe