{"type":"message","id":"201529f6","parentId":"7695eb3f","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:24:16.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the clawhub config shows `\"registry\": \"https://mirror-cn.clawhub.com\"` - this is a Chinese mirror. And the user is looking at `https://hub.cocoloop.cn/skills/666` - the cocoloop hub. Let me check if the installed capability-evolver is from the mirror or from the original npm.\n\nThe issue might be that the installed version (1.67.4 from npm @evomap/evolver) is different from what the cocoloop hub has (v1.27.3). The cocoloop hub version (v1.27.3) is likely the OpenClaw-adapted version.\n\n\nThe hub page describes capability-evolver as \"OpenClaw官方维护的 AI Agent 自我进化引擎\" - the official OpenClaw maintained version - which suggests the cocoloop version at v1.27.3 is specifically adapted for OpenClaw, whereas the npm version is the upstream EvoMap package. Since this skill was manually installed rather than through the clawhub CLI, it's probably the original npm package that needs to be replaced with the OpenClaw-adapted version.\n","thinkingSignature":"8a024ee3533a4b77d07f7a6503f1f49b2cc21d1bc5adbf3b484935e87f37589d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_54g3y096wl01_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 hub 上的 v1.27.3 和当前安装的版本的区别\n# 当前装的是 npm 原版 1.67.4，hub 上是 OpenClaw 适配版 1.27.3\n# cocoloop hub 的 registry\necho \"=== hub registry ===\"\ncat ~/.config/clawhub/config.json 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"=== cocoloop hub ===\"\ncurl -s --max-time 5 \"https://hub.cocoloop.cn/\" 2>&1 | head -5 || echo \"cannot reach cocoloop\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":295,"output":386,"cacheRead":137984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138665,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778851437298,"responseId":"0656516e5e732a716d6a2fdcd0747efd"}}
