10934375,8.5016661,6.541344134375,8.5016661,6.818844334375L8.5016661,12.567176734375L8.501666499999999,12.568011734375ZM12,14.588844734375L9.6708331,13.280510734375L9.6708331,10.505511234375L12,9.197177434375L14.329166,10.505510334375L14.329166,13.280510734375L12,14.588844734375ZM13.496666,20.613843734375C12.663333,20.613843734375,11.8908329,20.33717[... 184038 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778851458006}}
{"type":"message","id":"86a8bf95","parentId":"baeccc77","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:24:50.406Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The hub.cocoloop.cn page returned HTML that looks like a marketplace (not directly the skill content). The external content warning is blocking the full content. But I did get enough information from the earlier web fetch to understand what capability-evolver is.\n\nThe key finding is:\n- The user installed the npm version (1.67.4, which is the upstream EvoMap version)\n- But the hub version is 1.27.3, which is an OpenClaw-specific adaptation\n- These are fundamentally different versions - the npm one is NOT adapted for OpenClaw\n\nSo the issue is: the user installed from npm (@evomap/evolver) rather than from the OpenClaw-specific skill hub (cocoloop or clawhub).\n \nI need to clarify that capability-evolver is actually a meta-skill running externally to OpenClaw, not integrated into the agent's core workflow. The version mismatch is likely why it's not functioning properly within the OpenClaw environment. I should suggest the user switch to the cocoloop version (1.27.3) which is designed specifically for OpenClaw integration, or explore using OpenClaw's native tools like memory-core for continuous improvement instead.\n","thinkingSignature":"930a5c6f1efd1debc3972759da59baa32bc2cdfaf02247ad154f623877a736da"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n这个情况很有意思。你装的版本和 hub 上的版本**根本不是一回事**：\n\n**版本对比：**\n\n| 来源 | 版本 | 性质 |\n|------|------|------|\n| npm（你装的） | 1.67.4 | 上游原版，不认识 OpenClaw |\n| CocoLoop Hub | v1.27.3 | OpenClaw 适配版 |\n\n**你装错源了。** 你装的是 npm 上的 `@evomap/evolver`（上游原版），不是给 OpenClaw 用的版本。\n\n**那这个 skill 有没有用？**\n\n说实话：**它是外部工具，不是 OpenClaw 的核心功能**。它的工作方式是：\n\n1. 扫描 OpenClaw 的 session 日志文件\n2. 分析错误和信号\n3. 生成改动建议\n4. 尝试自动修改文件\n\n问题在于——**它的\"自我迭代\"逻辑是给通用 AI agent 用的**，不是给 OpenClaw 多 Agent 系统用的。它会把 session 里任何中文对话当信号，尝试改 155 个文件（因为它不认识你的多 Agent workspace 结构）。\n\n**两个选择：**\n\n1. **重新安装正确版本** — 从 CocoLoop Hub 装 v1.27.3（OpenClaw 适配版），而不是 npm 版本\n2. **关掉它** — 它每天跑但产生不了实际价值，白浪费 cron 资源\n\n要我去 CocoLoop Hub 重新安装正确版本，还是先关掉？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":132402,"output":556,"cacheRead":1088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134046,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778851466767,"responseId":"0656518b37bfef8337353265f7c45c0b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1750e828","parentId":"86a8bf95","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:28:27.028Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[message_id: om_x100b6f45b94c54a8c394b972ebb43e2]\nou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: 从 CocoLoop Hub 装 v1.27.3（OpenClaw 适配版）好用？"}],"timestamp":1778851707007}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6f45b94c54a8c394b972ebb43e2\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-05-15 21:28 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"a0162026","parentId":"1750e828","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:28:27.028Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"8660a174","parentId":"a0162026","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:28:53.179Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether installing the CocoLoop Hub version (v1.27.3) would work better. They're skeptical - asking if it would actually be useful.\n\nLet me think about this honestly. The CocoLoop version is specifically adapted for OpenClaw, but:\n\n1. The core issue I identified is fundamental - evolver reads session logs and tries to modify files based on \"signals\". The signal detection logic is what's causing it to pick up Chinese text and try to modify 155 files.\n\n2. The v1.27.3 OpenClaw adaptation might fix some issues but probably not the core signal detection problem.\n\n3. Even if it works \"better\", does it actually produce useful outcomes? The evolution system is designed to self-modify code, but OpenClaw's workspace has many agents with their own files. The evolver would need to understand this multi-agent structure to make meaningful improvements.\n\n4. The user's actual need seems to be: \"I want my AI system to automatically improve itself.\" But OpenClaw already has some self-improvement mechanisms (memory-core dreaming, lossless-claw compaction). The evolver is an ADDITIONAL external layer on top of these.\n\nI should be honest - the OpenClaw-adapted version would likely fix some technical issues (like signal detection for OpenClaw sessions), but the fundamental question of whether it produces meaningful improvements is still unclear.\n\nAlso, I need to check - can I actually install from a different registry? Let me think about this...\n\nThe clawhub CLI uses a registry. The user has it configured to mirror-cn.clawhub.com. The cocoloop hub at hub.cocoloop.cn might be a different marketplace altogether.\n\nLet me be honest with the user about whether this is worth doing.\n","thinkingSignature":"8fb85fd4c735294033775b7929d715f0805c2e1e2917ca1925f02676812792f6"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n说实话，我不太确定。原因是：\n\n**v1.27.3 会修复什么问题：**\n- 可能修复 signal 检测逻辑，更认识 OpenClaw 的 session 格式\n- 可能有更好的路径处理\n- 可能限制改动范围在合理范围内\n\n**但核心问题可能还在：**\n- evolver 的设计思路是\"改代码来自我进化\"\n- 但 OpenClaw 多 Agent 系统的改进不一定靠改代码，而是靠**记忆、上下文、协作流程**\n- 它可能还是会尝试改一堆文件，然后被 reject\n\n**更关键的问题：** 你装的是 npm 版 `@evomap/evolver`，不是 skill 形式。这说明你可能不是通过 OpenClaw skill 系统装的，而是直接 npm 安装的。这本身就是问题。\n\n**我建议：**\n1. 先从 clawhub 卸载掉当前的 capability-evolver\n2. 然后从 OpenClaw skill 系统重新安装（用 `clawhub install capability-evolver` 看能不能拉到 v1.27.3）\n3. 如果 clawhub 装不上，就直接关掉这个功能\n\n你觉得呢？是想试重新安装，还是先关掉等社区有更好的方案？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":125167,"output":597,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125764,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778851707166,"responseId":"0656527c519b9861b8cc9c35dc66ea96"}}
