{"type":"message","id":"953d69ec","parentId":"2539e14a","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:05:16.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why the \"tts\" (TK选品大师) agent keeps saying it doesn't have Feishu multi-dimensional table permissions, even though they've added it to the table's admin permissions.\n\nThis is likely a multi-account issue - the tts agent uses its own Feishu app (cli_a930f78f51399bc6), and the multi-dimensional table permission needs to be granted to that specific app's identity, not the user's personal account or the main kiit account.\n\nLet me think about this:\n1. The tts agent has its own Feishu app (appId: cli_a930f78f51399bc6, name: \"TK 选品大师\")\n\n\n2. Multi-dimensional table permissions in Feishu are granted at the app level, so I need to check whether the table was shared with the tts app or just with the user's account. If the tts agent is using a bot token to access the table, the bot itself needs to be invited as a member to that specific multi-dimensional table - regular table permissions won't automatically extend to app-level access.\n\nLet me check what the tts agent is actually configured to do, then test the permissions directly.","thinkingSignature":"014d72b1d610918b55b8e178f2374f5b4fcd10935293cac7ac11b2dcbdfd45b6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ynv3m6clhngr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 tts 的飞书配置\nlark-cli auth status --app-id cli_a930f78f51399bc6 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":186,"output":302,"cacheRead":129952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130440,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778853907300,"responseId":"06565b13c98517501c6725c251baef27"}}
