{"type":"message","id":"6b7aa877","parentId":"dac7f3d3","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:05:23.287Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nlfvarwkqxwi_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Global CLI configuration management\n\nUsage:\n  lark-cli config [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:\n  bind        Bind Agent config to a workspace (source / app-id / force)\n  default-as  View or set default identity type\n  init        Initialize configuration (app-id / app-secret-stdin / brand)\n  remove      Remove app configuration (clears all tokens and config)\n  show        Show current configuration\n  strict-mode View or set strict mode (identity restriction policy)\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help   help for config\n\nUse \"lark-cli config [command] --help\" for more information about a command."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":123,"aggregated":"Global CLI configuration management\n\nUsage:\n  lark-cli config [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:\n  bind        Bind Agent config to a workspace (source / app-id / force)\n  default-as  View or set default identity type\n  init        Initialize configuration (app-id / app-secret-stdin / brand)\n  remove      Remove app configuration (clears all tokens and config)\n  show        Show current configuration\n  strict-mode View or set strict mode (identity restriction policy)\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help   help for config\n\nUse \"lark-cli config [command] --help\" for more information about a command.","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778853923286}}
{"type":"message","id":"2aa8bdb8","parentId":"6b7aa877","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:05:30.163Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `lark-cli config list` command shows available commands, but not the actual config. Let me use `lark-cli config show` to see the current configuration.\n\nActually, the issue is that lark-cli only allows one identity configuration at a time. The user has multiple Feishu apps configured (kiit, tts, etc.), but lark-cli only stores one `appId` at a time.\n\nSo when the tts agent tries to use lark-cli, it might be using the wrong appId (the default one, not the tts-specific one).\n\nLet me check what the current config shows.","thinkingSignature":"d820062f21df29fa11c43d51d2efb8e0bdd0b7c1353f7a047d09c6bcdfa330d9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_822hzrdrcrn4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"lark-cli config show 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":194,"output":161,"cacheRead":130240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130595,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778853923415,"responseId":"06565b23fc0c187fa8c633c7e914f75a"}}
