{"type":"message","id":"e4a3d3ee","parentId":"368ae618","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:06:00.867Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The tts agent is using a different app (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) but `lark-cli config show` only shows the default profile (cli_a9558a1795799bb5 which is the agent-orchestrator app). The tts app doesn't have a lark-cli profile configured.\n\nThe issue is that the tts agent is trying to use lark-cli with its own app credentials, but the lark-cli is only configured with the agent-orchestrator app's credentials.\n\nI need to check how tts agent is configured to use feishu/lark. Let me check the feishu plugin configuration for the tts account.\n\nThe feishu plugin uses multiple app accounts. Each account has its own appId and appSecret. \n\nSo the real question is whether the tts agent's app (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) actually has permission to access the bitable. I should verify the app configuration and what permissions it currently has, then test whether it can reach the specific table tts is trying to access.","thinkingSignature":"1487e753957101b13359d922120965ca0e9fcb97455d163697f9a0b7a675eb32"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lupmjsf5kojt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 测试 tts 的 app 能不能访问 bitable\n# 先看看当前配置能访问哪些 app\nlark-cli config show 2>&1\necho \"---\"\n# 看 tts 的 app id\necho \"tts app: cli_a930f78f51399bc6\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":246,"output":310,"cacheRead":130656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131212,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778853952648,"responseId":"06565b41af9d97ada8e1f356abc157eb"}}
