{"type":"message","id":"a8ae7f4b","parentId":"cb808ffd","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:06:25.357Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now. `lark-cli config show` shows only one app (`cli_a9558a1795799bb5` - the main kiit app). But the tts agent uses a different app (`cli_a930f78f51399bc6`).\n\nThe `lark-cli` can only bind ONE app at a time for the CLI. But tts uses its own Feishu app. The tts agent is a separate OpenClaw agent with its own Feishu app. The lark-cli is a global CLI that only works with one app at a time.\n\nSo the question is: does the tts agent use `lark-cli` internally, or does it use the Feishu plugin API directly? If it's using lark-cli, then it would only work with the currently bound app (kiit's app, not tts's app).\n \nNow I'm realizing the Feishu plugin in OpenClaw is configured with multiple accounts—kiit and tts each have their own app credentials. The tts agent probably authenticates through the Feishu plugin, not the lark-cli. So the \"no permission\" error might stem from tts trying to access a bitable with its own app credentials, which either lacks the necessary permissions or the app itself doesn't have bitable access enabled.\n\nLet me check if the tts app actually has bitable permissions in its Feishu app configuration. Or maybe I should try checking what permissions the currently active app has and see if I can access bitable at all. The user mentioned adding tts to the table with admin permissions, but that might not be the core issue—tts could be making API calls that require specific scopes that aren't granted to its app.\n\nI'm wondering if the problem is simpler: tts might not even be using lark-cli and instead relies on direct API calls through OpenClaw's Feishu plugin. So I should clarify what tool tts is actually using to access the bitable, then test whether that specific tool has the right permissions for this operation.","thinkingSignature":"5d48aba64cb15af0d92061c3adcd0ddd5d5eb301eb5cbd6dc551de46c253bb99"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到问题了。\n\n**lark-cli 只能绑定一个 app**，当前绑定的是 `kiit` 的 app（`cli_a9558a1795799bb5`），但 **tts 用的是自己的 app**（`cli_a930f78f51399bc6`）。\n\n两个是不同的飞书应用，tts 的 app 可能：\n1. 没有开通多维表格权限\n2. 或者 lark-cli 绑定的是 kiit 的 app，tts 用自己的 app 走的是 OpenClaw Feishu 插件 API\n\n**先确认一下：**\n你说\"已经把他加入表格管理权限\" — 是把 tts 这个 **机器人 app** 加为多维表格的管理员，还是在飞书开发者后台给 tts 的 app 开通了多维表格权限？\n\n这两个是不一样的：\n- **加机器人到表格** = 给 app id 加成员权限\n- **开发者后台开通权限** = app 需要先申请多维表格相关的权限scope\n\n你在[飞书开发者后台](https://open.feishu.cn/app)里，tts 的 app（`cli_a930f78f51399bc6`）有没有开通这些权限？\n- `bitable:app`（多维表格）\n- `bitable:app:readonly`\n\n还是说你只是把机器人加到了表格里当管理员？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":228,"output":703,"cacheRead":130880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131811,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778853961195,"responseId":"06565b49a730b2734370221605f5a096"}}
