{"type":"message","id":"f67fa37d","parentId":"83b669f1","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:09:33.869Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking:\n1. How to fix the permission issue?\n2. Which Feishu app are other agents using?\n3. Is it independently installed CLI?\n\nLet me check what Feishu apps are configured for each agent in the OpenClaw config.\n","thinkingSignature":"f90452c0f05064e5594dc255b8c0cb6b443064a8600847cc828bf6d6811b5e26"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1tm10ujbc2l1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nc = json.load(sys.stdin)\naccounts = c['channels']['feishu']['accounts']\nfor name, info in accounts.items():\n    if isinstance(info, dict) and 'appId' in info:\n        print(f'{name}: appId={info[\\\"appId\\\"]}')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":131882,"output":156,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132038,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778854155674,"responseId":"06565c0c4aa1c50d7dc406d764e7278b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6bad32c1","parentId":"f67fa37d","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:09:34.039Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1tm10ujbc2l1_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"kiit: appId=cli_a93650c6fc785bce\ntts: appId=cli_a930f78f51399bc6\nagent-orchestrator: appId=cli_a9558a1795799bb5\ncontent: appId=cli_a978060ba7249bd8\ntraffic: appId=cli_a9365703ce78dbb5\nops: appId=cli_a954f94ade79dbcd\ndirector: appId=cli_a96d9bcb44b9dcba\nfinance: appId=cli_a96af4eceab99cb5\nreview: appId=cli_a954fb807f7adcd2\nkoc: appId=cli_a96af5b441f91bb5"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":55,"aggregated":"kiit: appId=cli_a93650c6fc785bce\ntts: appId=cli_a930f78f51399bc6\nagent-orchestrator: appId=cli_a9558a1795799bb5\ncontent: appId=cli_a978060ba7249bd8\ntraffic: appId=cli_a9365703ce78dbb5\nops: appId=cli_a954f94ade79dbcd\ndirector: appId=cli_a96d9bcb44b9dcba\nfinance: appId=cli_a96af4eceab99cb5\nreview: appId=cli_a954fb807f7adcd2\nkoc: appId=cli_a96af5b441f91bb5","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778854174039}}
{"type":"message","id":"748209f2","parentId":"6bad32c1","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:09:47.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see clearly - there are 10 Feishu apps (accounts), each with a different appId. The `lark-cli` only binds ONE app at a time. Currently it's bound to `kiit` (`cli_a93650c6fc785bce`), but wait - actually looking at the config show earlier it showed `cli_a9558a1795799bb5` which is `agent-orchestrator`. Let me check which one is actually bound.\n\nActually the config showed: `appId: \"cli_a9558a1795799bb5\"` which is `agent-orchestrator`. But the user's question is: do OTHER agents use the independently installed `lark-cli`?\n \nSo the key insight is that each OpenClaw agent authenticates with its own dedicated Feishu app through the Feishu plugin, not through `lark-cli`. The `lark-cli` is just a standalone CLI tool - the agents are getting their Feishu integration directly via the API. The `lark-cli` isn't actually involved in agent-to-Feishu communication at all.\n\nBut if the user is saying the tts agent can't access bitable, that's strange since tts should be using its own app credentials through the Feishu plugin. Let me figure out what's actually broken here. The tts agent is reporting \"no Feishu bitable permission,\" but each OpenClaw agent has its own independent Feishu app - so tts's API calls should be using its own app's credentials, which might not have bitable enabled in the Feishu developer console, or there's some configuration issue with how the Feishu plugin is handling bitable access. I'm realizing I need to see the actual error the user is getting rather than guessing at the cause. Let me think about this differently—instead of continuing down the lark-cli path, I should look at what OpenClaw's docs actually say about connecting Feishu apps to agents, since that's probably where the real issue lies. The real issue is likely that tts's app doesn't have the bitable permission scope enabled in the Feishu developer console, so the agent can't actually read the table data when it queries through the API.\n","thinkingSignature":"78b7bf6ae1ffa07d20220a78d717c2ea55dc438d816c2d899fed4f7bae0891e8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_loz0djxa7wp3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查各个 agent 的 app 对应的名称\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nc = json.load(sys.stdin)\naccounts = c['channels']['feishu']['accounts']\nfor name, info in accounts.items():\n    if isinstance(info, dict) and 'appId' in info:\n        app_id = info['appId']\n        name_field = info.get('name', '(no name)')\n        enabled = info.get('enabled', '?')\n        print(f'{name}: appId={app_id}, name={name_field}, enabled={enabled}')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":292,"output":609,"cacheRead":131872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132773,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778854174168,"responseId":"06565c1fca5fce97dd540e764935b1e8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e9d0264","parentId":"748209f2","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:09:47.809Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_loz0djxa7wp3_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"kiit: appId=cli_a93650c6fc785bce, name=(no name), enabled=True\ntts: appId=cli_a930f78f51399bc6, name=TK 选品大师, enabled=True\nagent-orchestrator: appId=cli_a9558a1795799bb5, name=Agent 编掔工程师, enabled=True\ncontent: appId=cli_a978060ba7249bd8, name=🎬 内容专家, enabled=True\ntraffic: appId=cli_a9365703ce78dbb5, name=📢 投流专家, enabled=True\nops: appId=cli_a954f94ade79dbcd, name=📊 运营助手, enabled=True\ndirector: appId=cli_a96d9bcb44b9dcba, name=🧭 运营总监, enabled=True\nfinance: appId=cli_a96af4eceab99cb5, name=💰 财务助手, enabled=True\nreview: appId=cli_a954fb807f7adcd2, name=💬 评论专家, enabled=True\nkoc: appId=cli_a96af5b441f91bb5, name=🤝 达人运营, enabled=True"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":55,"aggregated":"kiit: appId=cli_a93650c6fc785bce, name=(no name), enabled=True\ntts: appId=cli_a930f78f51399bc6, name=TK 选品大师, enabled=True\nagent-orchestrator: appId=cli_a9558a1795799bb5, name=Agent 编掔工程师, enabled=True\ncontent: appId=cli_a978060ba7249bd8, name=🎬 内容专家, enabled=True\ntraffic: appId=cli_a9365703ce78dbb5, name=📢 投流专家, enabled=True\nops: appId=cli_a954f94ade79dbcd, name=📊 运营助手, enabled=True\ndirector: appId=cli_a96d9bcb44b9dcba, name=🧭 运营总监, enabled=True\nfinance: appId=cli_a96af4eceab99cb5, name=💰 财务助手, enabled=True\nreview: appId=cli_a954fb807f7adcd2, name=💬 评论专家, enabled=True\nkoc: appId=cli_a96af5b441f91bb5, name=🤝 达人运营, enabled=True","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778854187809}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d160f94","parentId":"3e9d0264","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:10:04.179Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Each agent has its own Feishu app. And the lark-cli is currently bound to the agent-orchestrator app (cli_a9558a1795799bb5), not to the tts app.\n\nThe lark-cli is a global CLI tool. It can only be bound to one app at a time. Currently it's bound to the agent-orchestrator app.\n\nWhen tts tries to access bitable, it likely uses the Feishu MCP tools or direct API calls through OpenClaw's Feishu plugin. Each agent has its own Feishu app, and the Feishu plugin handles authentication per agent.\n \nSo the user is asking two things: how to fix the bitable permission issue for tts, and which Feishu app the other agents are using—whether they're independent installs or tied to the lark-cli binding.\n\nLooking at the architecture, each agent actually has its own dedicated Feishu app embedded in the OpenClaw config, and the Feishu plugin manages authentication separately for each one. The lark-cli operates independently with just one app bound at a time. For the bitable permissions specifically, tts is probably using direct Feishu API calls through its app, so the issue likely comes down to whether that app has the right permissions granted in the Feishu developer console—since lark-cli and the Feishu plugin work independently of each other.","thinkingSignature":"83523d309a868ed28cdd567bc21b997d6f3ac836d67f318142fc82a7540b0761"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n每个 Agent 都是独立的飞书应用，用的是 OpenClaw 的 Feishu 插件认证，不是 lark-cli。\n\n**当前架构：**\n\n| Agent | 飞书 App | 用途 |\n|-------|---------|------|\n| kiit（你用的） | cli_a93650c6fc785bce | 主应用 |\n| tts（选品大师） | cli_a930f78f51399bc6 | 选品 |\n| agent-orchestrator | cli_a9558a1795799bb5 | 绑定了 lark-cli |\n| content | cli_a978060ba7249bd8 | 内容 |\n| traffic | cli_a9365703ce78dbb5 | 投流 |\n| ... | ... | ... |\n\nlark-cli 是单独工具，只绑定了一个 app，跟各个 Agent 的飞书应用**互相不影响**。\n\n**tts 没有多维表格权限的原因：**\n\ntts 用的是 `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` 这个飞书应用，它的 **app 权限**需要在[飞书开发者后台](https://open.feishu.cn/app)单独开通：\n\n1. 打开 https://open.feishu.cn/app\n2. 找到 `cli_a930f78f51399bc6`（TK 选品大师）\n3. **权限管理** → 搜索 `bitable` → 开通：\n   - `bitable:app`（多维表格读写）\n   - `bitable:app:readonly`（可选，只读）\n4. 发布版本\n\n**如果 app 已经有权限**，问题可能是：\n- 多维表格本身没有把 tts 的 app 加为成员/管理员\n- tts 访问的表格 ID 不对\n\n你在飞书开发者后台给 tts 的 app 开通多维表格权限了吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":440,"output":675,"cacheRead":132160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133275,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778854188171,"responseId":"06565c2cb8b811037db456bf876fe875"}}
